intro: Trisetella trichaete, commonly known as the hairy trisetella, is a species of flowering plant belonging to the family Apiaceae. It is characterized by its slender, branched stems and small, greenish-yellow flowers that appear in umbels. The plant has finely hairy leaves and is typically found in grassy areas and disturbed soils. It is native to parts of Europe and Asia and is often used in horticulture for its ornamental value. Due to its delicate appearance, it is sometimes cultivated in gardens for its visual appeal.
